Our CI pipeline has started failing intermittently on the integration test suite. About 30% of runs fail with this error:

```
TEST FAILURE: test_concurrent_order_processing
  Expected: order.status == 'fulfilled'
  Actual:   order.status == 'processing'

  at tests/integration/orders.test.js:145
  at async Promise.all (tests/integration/orders.test.js:130)
```

```javascript
// tests/integration/orders.test.js (lines 125-150)
test('test_concurrent_order_processing', async () => {
  const orders = await Promise.all([
    createOrder({ item: 'widget', qty: 1 }),
    createOrder({ item: 'gadget', qty: 2 }),
    createOrder({ item: 'doohickey', qty: 1 }),
  ]);

  // Process all orders concurrently
  await Promise.all(orders.map(o => processOrder(o.id)));

  // Wait for async processing
  await sleep(2000);

  // Verify all orders are fulfilled
  for (const order of orders) {
    const updated = await getOrder(order.id);
    expect(updated.status).toBe('fulfilled'); // <-- FAILS HERE intermittently
  }
});
```

```javascript
// src/services/orderProcessor.js
async function processOrder(orderId) {
  await db.query('UPDATE orders SET status = $1 WHERE id = $2', ['processing', orderId]);
  // Queue async fulfillment job
  await jobQueue.add('fulfill', { orderId });
  return { queued: true };
}

// src/workers/fulfillment.js
module.exports = async function fulfill(job) {
  const { orderId } = job.data;
  // ... fulfillment logic (takes 500ms-3000ms depending on inventory checks)
  await db.query('UPDATE orders SET status = $1 WHERE id = $2', ['fulfilled', orderId]);
};
```

CI environment: Node 18, PostgreSQL 14, Redis 7 (for job queue). Tests run in a Docker container. The test was written 3 months ago and started failing about 2 weeks ago. No code changes to the order processing in that time.

Recent CI environment changes:
- 2 weeks ago: upgraded CI runner from 4-core to 2-core machines (cost savings)
- 1 week ago: bumped Node from 18.17 to 18.19 (no changelog items seem relevant)
